theorem P3_iff_isOpen_of_isClosed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsClosed A) :
    Topology.P3 A ↔ IsOpen A := by
  constructor
  · intro hP3
    -- `closure A = A` because `A` is closed
    have h_closure : closure A = A := hA.closure_eq
    -- From `P3`, we have `A ⊆ interior (closure A)`; rewrite using `h_closure`
    have h_sub1 : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior A := by
      simpa [h_closure] using hP3
    -- The interior is always contained in the set
    have h_sub2 : interior A ⊆ A := interior_subset
    -- Hence `interior A = A`
    have h_eq : interior A = A := Subset.antisymm h_sub2 h_sub1
    -- Therefore `A` is open
    have h_open_int : IsOpen (interior A) := isOpen_interior
    simpa [h_eq] using h_open_int
  · intro hOpen
    exact Topology.P3_of_open hOpen

theorem P3_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] :
    Topology.P3 (∅ : Set X) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hx
  cases hx
